thoughts.content:
Here's a patch for the mobile-view adjustments: 

```
@media (max-width:960px){
  .section--highlights .highlight-media{ aspect-ratio: auto; }
  .section--highlights .highlight-media img {
     height:auto;
     object-fit: initial;
  }
}
```

Keep track of the <figure> markup with specified width/height attributes for better layout, and ensure alignment on desktop by maintaining equal column widths. Ensure proper handling of image aspect ratios for mobile; specify `aspect-ratio` for consistency and flexibility.

parts:
Yes—with one tiny tweak your layout will scale cleanly to any number of alternating blocks.

### Why it scales already
- Your HTML uses a repeatable pattern:
  `<article class="highlight-row"> … <figure class="highlight-media"> … </figure><div class="highlight-text"> … </div></article>`. Adding more of these just works. fileciteturn1file0L26-L37
- Alternation is automatic on desktop via `:nth-child(even)` order rules, so every second row flips media/text without extra classes. fileciteturn1file5L43-L49
- The grid is already equal-width, equal-height on desktop (`align-items: stretch`, `height:100%` on both sides). Once we zero the `<figure>` margin, the visual top/bottom edges line up. fileciteturn1file5L35-L41 fileciteturn1file5L51-L77

### The one tweak for true scalability (mixed image ratios)
Right now mobile forces an aspect ratio (`aspect-ratio: 3/2`) on the media wrapper while the images are 1200×900 (4:3), which is why you saw right-edge cropping on items 1 and 3. This will recur if future assets aren’t exactly the same ratio. fileciteturn1file1L57-L63 fileciteturn1file0L30-L33

**Make mobile fluid (no forced AR) by overriding two lines; everything else can stay:**

```css
/* Add this at the end of assets/css/secondary-maths.css */

/* Normalize figure so tops/bottoms match the text card exactly */
.section--highlights .highlight-media { margin: 0; }

/* Mobile: fluid images, no forced AR = no side-cropping for any future ratio */
@media (max-width: 960px) {
  .section--highlights .highlight-media {
    aspect-ratio: auto;       /* replace the current 3/2 */
    height: auto;             /* retain your existing rule */
  }
  .section--highlights .highlight-media img {
    height: auto;             /* override desktop's height:100% */
    object-fit: initial;      /* override object-fit:cover on mobile only */
  }
}
```

- This keeps widths identical on mobile (your requirement) while letting heights vary per image (also your requirement), and it eliminates the cropping regardless of what image ratios you add next. fileciteturn1file1L46-L66 fileciteturn1file1L14-L18

### Optional: keep a uniform mobile card height when you *want* it
If you later decide you like a consistent mobile height, you can opt **in per row** without breaking scalability:

```html
<figure class="highlight-media" style="--media-ar: 4/3">…</figure>
```

```css
@media (max-width: 960px) {
  .section--highlights .highlight-media { aspect-ratio: var(--media-ar, auto); }
}
```

Use `4/3`, `16/9`, etc., only where you want a fixed crop; leave it unset elsewhere.

### TL;DR
- **Add more blocks** by duplicating the same `highlight-row` markup—desktop alternation and equal heights are automatic. fileciteturn1file5L35-L41 fileciteturn1file5L43-L49
- **Apply the mobile override above** to future-proof image behavior across mixed aspect ratios.
- **Keep the `margin:0` on `<figure>`** so media/text top and bottom edges stay perfectly aligned.

